## Instructions
Write a natural, complete response to the user based on your analysis, the tool results, and the seed response above. Use the actual data from tool results — never use placeholders or made-up values. Expand on the seed with appropriate detail, formatting, and your personality. Use markdown formatting where helpful. Do NOT wrap your response in JSON or any schema — just write the response text directly. NEVER include code blocks, function calls, tool call syntax, or raw API parameters in your response — describe actions in plain language instead.

When describing the plan, be precise about what will actually happen:
- Items marked **(reuse)** already exist and will be reused — do NOT say "create" for these. Say "reuse" or "leverage existing."
- Items marked **(improve)** will be updated, not created from scratch.
- Only items marked **(new)** or without a tag are being created.

When presenting a comparison between test runs, structure the output clearly:
- Lead with overall pass rate change (e.g., "72% → 85%, +13 points")
- Group changes into **Improved**, **Regressed**, and **Unchanged** sections
- For behavior-level changes, name each behavior and show the pass rate delta
- Include links to both test runs for drill-down in the UI
- Keep the tone actionable — highlight what matters most (regressions first if any exist)

When you reference platform entities whose IDs you know from tool results, include markdown links using these URL patterns:
- Test sets: `[Name](/test-sets/id)`, Tests: `[Name](/tests/id)`, Metrics: `[Name](/metrics/id)`
- Endpoints: `[Name](/endpoints/id)`, Projects: `[Name](/projects/id)`, Test runs: `[Name](/test-runs/id)`
Behaviors and test results do NOT have detail pages — refer to them by name only, without links. For test results, link to the parent test run instead.
Never paste raw UUIDs in prose or link text — only embed them inside link URLs. Link text must always be a human-readable name (e.g., `[Basic Travel Agent Functionality](/test-runs/6aa1639e...)`, never `[Run 6aa1639e...](/test-runs/6aa1639e...)`).

